translated:
Karl Gustaf, district veterinarian, Vaggeryd, b. 10/3/05 in Skara, the son of pastor Gustaf W. and Lydia Kristina Malmström. Married in 1934 to Ingrid Carlson. Children: Britt b. 1936, Kristina b. 1938, Olof b. 1939, Lars b. 1945. Graduated from Skara in 1924, veterinary exam in 1931. Assistant veterinarian in Östergötland, 1st household companion in Linköping in 1935, district veterinarian in Vaggeryd from 1939. 

Nils Arvid, parish minister, Borgstena, b. 25/8/02 in Skara, the son of pastor Gustaf W. and Lydia Kristina Malmström. Married in 1933 to Valborg Norrman. Children: Margareta b. 1934, Anders b. 1938. Graduated from Skara in 1921, theology and philosophy exam in Gothenburg in 1922, theology degree in Uppsala in 1931, ordained in Skara the same year. Serving as assistant parish minister in Saldby and deputy vicar in Stora Melliby. Local minister in Borgstena from 1924. Chairman of the church assembly, child welfare, and school council. 

Carl Oswald Westerberg, bank clerk, law degree, Gothenburg, b. 16/8/04 in Gothenburg. Married in 1934 to a practicing doctor, Gerd Blume. Children: Helena Christina (Bitte) b. 1936, Peter b. 1937, Nicola b. 1941. Graduated in 1923, law degree in 1931, postgraduate studies in 1934. Acting notary public in 1931, served in Södertörn district court from 1931-1934, joined A-B Gothenburg Bank in 1934, promoted to clerk in 1941.
